<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="544" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,789]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,188,213]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">Discussion:</emphasis>
The present specimens fit well in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[899,1008,188,212]" class="Gastropoda" family="Seguenziidae" genus="Halystina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seguenziida" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[899,1008,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">Halystina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall" box="[1193,1381,188,213]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" refString="Marshall, B. A. (1991) Mollusca Gastropoda: Seguenziidae from New Caledonia and the Loyalty Islands. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle A, 150, 41 - 109." type="journal article" year="1991">
<collectingCountry box="[1193,1293,188,213]" name="Marshall Islands" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">Marshall</collectingCountry>
(
<number box="[1315,1373,188,212]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and corresponding to the 
<taxonomicName box="[392,506,224,247]" class="Gastropoda" family="Seguenziidae" genus="Seguenzia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seguenziida" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[392,506,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">Seguenzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group III 
<emphasis box="[630,692,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Quinn" box="[700,870,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" refString="Quinn, J. F. Jr. (1983 b) A revision of the Seguenziacea Verrill, 1884 (Gastropoda: Prosobranchia). I. Summary and evaluation of the Superfamily. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 96 (4), 725 - 757." type="journal article" year="1983" yearSuffix="b">
Quinn (
<number box="[787,847,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" value="1983.0">1983</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
. The genus is known almost exclusively from the South Pacific, with a single species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Barnard, 1963" authorityName="Barnard" authorityYear="1963" box="[562,871,260,285]" class="Gastropoda" family="Seguenziidae" genus="Halystina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seguenziida" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis box="[562,682,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">H. simplex</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Barnard" box="[697,862,260,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" refString="Barnard, K. H. (1963) Contributions to the knowledge of South African marine Mollusca. Part IV. Gastropoda: Prosobranchiata: Rhipidoglossa, Docoglossa, Tectibranchiata. Polyplacophora. Solenogastres. Scaphopoda. Annals of the South African Museum, 47 (2), 201 - 360." type="journal article" year="1963">
Barnard, 
<number box="[803,862,260,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" value="1963.0">1963</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, occurring off Cape Point, 
<collectingCountry box="[1175,1319,260,285]" name="South Africa" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">South Africa</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" refString="Marshall, B. A. (1991) Mollusca Gastropoda: Seguenziidae from New Caledonia and the Loyalty Islands. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle A, 150, 41 - 109." type="journal article" year="1991">
<collectingCountry box="[1335,1436,260,285]" name="Marshall Islands" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">Marshall</collectingCountry>
<number box="[151,210,296,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Poppe" box="[224,431,295,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" refString="Poppe G. T., Tagaro S. P. &amp; Dekker H. (2006) The Seguenziidae, Chilodontidae, Trochidae, Calliostomatidae and Solariellidae of the Philippine Islands. Visaya, 2 (Supplement), 1 - 228." type="journal article" year="2006">
Poppe 
<emphasis box="[303,353,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[370,431,295,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The genus is diagnosed by its small size, overall rounded shell profile, with flat-sided whorls and finely granulate protoconch (
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall" box="[608,773,332,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" refString="Marshall, B. A. (1991) Mollusca Gastropoda: Seguenziidae from New Caledonia and the Loyalty Islands. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle A, 150, 41 - 109." type="journal article" year="1991">
<collectingCountry box="[608,709,332,357]" name="Marshall Islands" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">Marshall</collectingCountry>
<number box="[716,773,332,356]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and is probably related to the very similar genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall" authorityName="Marshall" class="Gastropoda" family="Seguenziidae" genus="Halystes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1340,1436,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">Halystes</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[151,253,367,392]" name="Marshall Islands" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">Marshall</collectingCountry>
</taxonomicName>
, which differs almost exclusively by its much larger size (
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall" box="[903,1071,367,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" refString="Marshall, B. A. (1988) New Seguenziidae (Mollusca: Gastropoda) from the Tasman, South Pacific, and Southern Antilles Basins. New Zealand Journal of Zoology, 15, 235 - 247. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 03014223.1988.10422618" type="journal article" year="1988">
<collectingCountry box="[903,1004,367,392]" name="Marshall Islands" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">Marshall</collectingCountry>
<number box="[1011,1071,368,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" value="1988.0">1988</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,789]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">
The present specimens are reminiscent of most of its congeners, but can be diagnosed by its more rounded overall profile, with a broader body whorl and a more step-like spire, a distinct concave region below the suture, fainter spiral cords (which gives the whorls a more convex profile) and its more delicate and narrowly spaced teleoconch sculpture. The present record greatly expands the distribution of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1022,1131,512,536]" class="Gastropoda" family="Seguenziidae" genus="Halystina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seguenziida" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1022,1131,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">Halystina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to western South Atlantic waters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="544" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,789]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">
<taxonomicName box="[199,419,584,608]" class="Gastropoda" family="Seguenziidae" genus="Halystina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seguenziida" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="umberlee">
<emphasis box="[199,419,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">Halystina umberlee</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 1991" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="1991" box="[626,929,583,608]" class="Gastropoda" family="Seguenziidae" genus="Halystina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seguenziida" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vaubani">
<emphasis box="[626,751,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">H. vaubani</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall" box="[757,929,583,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" refString="Marshall, B. A. (1991) Mollusca Gastropoda: Seguenziidae from New Caledonia and the Loyalty Islands. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle A, 150, 41 - 109." type="journal article" year="1991">
<collectingCountry box="[757,859,583,608]" name="Marshall Islands" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">Marshall</collectingCountry>
, 
<number box="[871,929,584,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by its broader body whorl, more delicate teleoconch sculpture and fainter spiral cords. 
<taxonomicName box="[911,1133,620,644]" class="Gastropoda" family="Seguenziidae" genus="Halystina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seguenziida" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="umberlee">
<emphasis box="[911,1133,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">Halystina umberlee</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="Thiele, 1925" authorityName="Thiele" authorityYear="1925" box="[151,487,655,680]" class="Gastropoda" family="Seguenziidae" genus="Halystina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seguenziida" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="siberutensis">
<emphasis box="[151,319,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">H. siberutensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Thiele" box="[333,479,655,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" refString="Thiele J. (1925) Gastropoden der Deutschen Tiefsee-Expedition. Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Deutschen Tiefsee- Expedition II, Teil 17 (2), 35 - 382." type="journal article" year="1925">
Thiele, 
<number box="[420,479,655,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" value="1925.0">1925</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 1991" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="1991" box="[498,831,655,680]" class="Gastropoda" family="Seguenziidae" genus="Halystina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seguenziida" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="caledonica">
<emphasis box="[498,655,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">H. caledonica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall" box="[662,831,655,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" refString="Marshall, B. A. (1991) Mollusca Gastropoda: Seguenziidae from New Caledonia and the Loyalty Islands. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle A, 150, 41 - 109." type="journal article" year="1991">
<collectingCountry box="[662,764,655,680]" name="Marshall Islands" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">Marshall</collectingCountry>
, 
<number box="[775,831,656,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Poppe, Tagaro &amp; Dekker, 2006" authorityName="Poppe, Tagaro &amp; Dekker" authorityYear="2006" box="[884,1368,655,680]" class="Gastropoda" family="Seguenziidae" genus="Halystina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seguenziida" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="globulus">
<emphasis box="[884,1014,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">H. globulus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Poppe" box="[1021,1368,655,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" refString="Poppe G. T., Tagaro S. P. &amp; Dekker H. (2006) The Seguenziidae, Chilodontidae, Trochidae, Calliostomatidae and Solariellidae of the Philippine Islands. Visaya, 2 (Supplement), 1 - 228." type="journal article" year="2006">
Poppe, Tagaro &amp; Dekker, 
<number box="[1312,1368,655,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by its more rounded profile, more convex whorls and more step-like spire. Finally, it can be easily differentiated from 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Seguenziidae" genus="Halystina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seguenziida" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">H. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 1991" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="1991" box="[291,599,727,752]" class="Gastropoda" family="Seguenziidae" genus="Carenzia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seguenziida" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis box="[291,420,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">H. carinata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall" box="[427,599,727,752]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" refString="Marshall, B. A. (1991) Mollusca Gastropoda: Seguenziidae from New Caledonia and the Loyalty Islands. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle A, 150, 41 - 109." type="journal article" year="1991">
<collectingCountry box="[427,529,727,752]" name="Marshall Islands" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">Marshall</collectingCountry>
, 
<number box="[541,599,728,752]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which have more angular shell profiles similar to specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Jeffreys, 1876" authorityName="Jeffreys" authorityYear="1876" class="Gastropoda" family="Seguenziidae" genus="Seguenzia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Seguenziida" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1322,1436,728,751]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="544">Seguenzia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jeffreys" box="[151,312,764,789]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" refString="Jeffreys, J. G. (1876) Preliminary report of the biological results of a cruise in H. M. S. Valorous to Davis Straits in 1875. Proceedings of the Royal Society, 25, 177 - 237. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1098 / rspl. 1876.0043" type="journal article" year="1876">
Jeffreys, 
<number box="[253,312,764,789]" pageId="8" pageNumber="544" value="1876.0">1876</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
